d for an FFP detection. Thus, unless \${\textbackslash}Gamma\$ is doubled, FFP detection will be driven into the (large-\${\textbackslash}theta\_*\$, small-\${\textbackslash}mu\$) corner of parameter space, reducing the detections by a net factor of 2 and cutting off the lowest-mass FFPs.},
